The leaflet is one page and mostly numbers: what the Pacto holds down, for whom, signed by whom. At the gates men read it and fold it into shirt pockets, which is where arguments are carried when they have been accepted. Twenty years of work, and history itself has taken over the agitprop. July is seven months away.
